kaffe.transformers module¶

A collection of graph transforms.

A transformer is a callable that accepts a graph and returns a transformed version.

class kaffe.transformers.BatchNormPreprocessor[source]¶

Bases: object

Prescale batch normalization parameters. Concatenate gamma (scale) and beta (bias) terms if set.

class kaffe.transformers.BatchNormScaleBiasFuser[source]¶

Bases: kaffe.transformers.SubNodeFuser

The original batch normalization paper includes two learned parameters: a scaling factor gamma and a bias eta. Caffe’s implementation does not include these two. However, it is commonly replicated by adding a scaling+bias layer immidiately after the batch norm.

This fuser merges the scaling+bias layer with the batch norm.
